pageContext.claim: “[Wisconsin] is a great state, but you had your best economic year that you've ever had, so that's great.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false. Wisconsin’s real gross domestic product grew 2.5 percent in 2018, the second largest increase in the Midwest and the state’s strongest year of economic growth since 2010. Wisconsin now ranks 17th in the country last year for economic growth, but it grew slower than the national average.
